performance is evaluated using a range of metrics (e.g., out-of-sample root-mean-squared error 
(RMSE)), and the best-performing models are selected for further analysis.

the variable and model selections:  
• A big data approach in variable selection is developed to enhance the coverage of potential 
predictors of economic growth and reduces the lag between real-world events and nowcasts.

Potential Policy Responses: Structural reforms to enhance productivity and competitiveness, as envisaged 
under NDS3 and the QNV 2030, would help raise private investment and reduce the saving-investment gap. 
Fiscal prudence should be preserved, revenue diversification toward non-hydrocarbon sources accelerated, and 
spending reoriented to support the reform agenda. These factors will reduce the current gap and help align the 
external position in the medium term.
